[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] There are two ways to mock functions: Either by creating a mock function to use in test code, or writing a `manual mock` to override a module dependency.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] Let's imagine we're testing an implementation of a function `forEach`, which invokes a callback for each item in a supplied array.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] To test this function, we can use a mock function, and inspect the mock's state to ensure the callback is invoked as expected.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] All mock functions have this special `.mock` property, which is where data about how the function has been called and what the function returned is kept.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] Mock functions are also very effective in code that uses a functional continuation-passing style.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] Code written in this style helps avoid the need for complicated stubs that recreate the behavior of the real component they're standing in for, in favor of injecting values directly into the test right before they're used.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] Most real-world examples actually involve getting ahold of a mock function on a dependent component and configuring that, but the technique is the same.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] In these cases, try to avoid the temptation to implement logic inside of any function that's not directly being tested.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] Suppose we have a class that fetches users from our API.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] Now, in order to test this method without actually hitting the API (and thus creating slow and fragile tests), we can use the `jest.mock(...)` function to automatically mock the axios module.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] Once we mock the module we can provide a `mockResolvedValue` for `.get` that returns the data we want our test to assert against.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] In effect, we are saying that we want `axios.get('/users.json')` to return a fake response.
[src:jest-testing/mock-functions] Still, there are cases where it's useful to go beyond the ability to specify return values and full-on replace the implementation of a mock function.
